litischen Sprachhandelns wie etwa Facebook, Twitter oder Rapid Response in den Blickpunkt genommen. Exemplarische Einzelanalysen ausgewählter Textsorten und Diskurse demonstrieren die Leistungsfähigkeit des in diesem Arbeitsheft vorgestellten Modells zur Analyse politischen Sprachhandelns. Literaturhinweise und Übungen, die zur Vertiefung des Stoffes beitragen, runden die einzelnen Kapitel ab.  aPolitical action is first and foremost verbal action. This study aims to give students and teachers a solid introductory foundation to the field of “Language and Politics” as well as to demonstrate the potential of a linguistic approach. The individual chapters are rounded out with references and exercises that add depth to the material.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aCommunication in politicsxGermany. 0aCommunication in politicszGermany. 0aGerman languagevPolitical aspects. 0aGerman languagexPolitical aspects. 0aGerman languagexSpoken German. 4aPolitische Rhetorik. 4aPolitolinguistik. 4aSprache und Politik. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Communication Studies.2bisacsh  aLanguage and Politics.  aPolitical Linguistics.  aPolitical Rhetoric.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2015 Part 1z978311076251808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2015z9783110438710oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97831103740870 cprintz978311033800340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311033866940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110338669423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110338669/original  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG P